data.title: People power
data.meta_description: Huge demonstrations in Hong Kong have forced its chief executive, Tung Chee-hwa, to delay implementation of a controversial anti-subversion law. This has raised questions about Mr Tung’s position, about whether Beijing can prevent a move to fuller democracy in Hong Kong, and about the effect that the crisis will have on the mainland | News
data.text:
Huge demonstrations in Hong Kong have forced its chief executive, Tung Chee-hwa, to delay implementation of a controversial anti-subversion law. This has raised questions about Mr Tung’s position, about whether Beijing can prevent a move to fuller democracy in Hong Kong, and about the effect that the crisis will have on the mainland

Jul 14th 2003|

Reuters
